00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
For this next problem, imagine you're the captain of a ship on the high seas.

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:07.000
And you know there's some enemy ship about 200 m away.

00:00:07.000 --> 00:00:09.000
You want to aim your cannon at some angle α,

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:14.000
and shoot the cannonball with some initial velocity of v¬ such that you hit the enemy ship.

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:19.000
Unfortunately, there's this 40-m tall iceberg about 110 m away from you,

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:23.000
which makes your shot a lot more difficult because you have to go over the iceberg.

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:29.000
So what angle α and initial speed v¬ should you use such that you hit the enemy ship?

00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:31.000
Now, there are actually a lot of answers here.

00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:34.000
But we're just looking for one that works. The one that works will hit the enemy ship.

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:36.000
And not hit the iceberg.

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:40.000
To answer this question, we're going to use a slightly different form of input than we normally do.

